args:
Having defeated the ancient weapon, the prince
and his party return to Saint Lotier. Both Ranzal
and {player_name} earn the trust of
Zacharias, and the Aquapolis agrees to forge
an alliance with New Alberia.
Truly impressive, {player_name}.\nYou dispatched that lost wonder with ease!
It was a most elucidating fight indeed.
You really never know what riches\nthese ruins hold until you get them\nup and moving again.
What exactly are you after here, Phares?

I've told you: research. The quest
for knowledge, of the civilization
that rose and fell before our time.
Knowledge of our very world itself!
This has nothing to do with Dyrenell,\nby the way. I'm merely a scholar at play.
If he claims he did not act in malice,\nI will lower my spear for now.
I claim neutrality. Nothing more or less.\nBut know that a storm is brewing, my\nbrother—one fit to take the entire world.
This storm began the day you awoke to the\ndragon's power.
What bearing do my actions have on the\nfate of the world?
I'll spare you the lecture for now. Just\nknow that not all storms are unwelcome.
Strong winds have a way of exposing\nsecrets long buried in the ground.
For now, I bid you farewell. Until next\ntime, my dear {player_name}.
I pray our next meeting will not be as foes.
Guess that's the end of it.
Saint Lotier should be safe for now, yeah?
Sadly, I doubt that'll do much to goad my\nold man into signin' an alliance.
But if I agree to return...
You've done well, and fought bravely.
But it is not enough to accept New Alberia\nas a peer. You are welcome to toil further\nto inspire greater trust...
Or you could return Ranzal to me.\nPerhaps then we could speak of alliance.
You can drop the act, Pops.
I'll come home. Just hurry up and sign an\nalliance with—
I'm afraid you can't have him.
Not even if it is a necessary condition of\nour alliance.
Your son is an irreplaceable part of our\nkingdom, Zacharias.
I know he may have been...impulsive when\nhe was younger, but those days are gone.
He is brave and wise in equal measure,\nand willing to dirty his hands in order to\nprotect others.
A New Alberia without Ranzal would be an\nunfitting alliance partner with a city as\ngreat as Saint Lotier.
I simply can't afford to lose him.
He is an integral asset of New Alberia.\nWe are a kingdom made by our people.
Well, hell, {player_name}...\nI don't know what to say.
If you would defy me in this matter,\nwe have nothing further to speak of.
Your paltry kingdom will be a colony.\nIt certainly merits no better!
I will dispatch a lieutenant of Saint Lotier\nimmediately to oversee your actions there.
Then you would annex us by force? I'd not\nthought the great Aquapolis would stoop\nto base tyranny!
Silence! I will not be questioned.
Enjoy languishing under the oppressive\neye of a lieutenant backed with the full\nauthority of Saint Lotier!
Wait, I'M the lieutenant of Saint Lotier?
Indeed, you will keep watch over New\nAlberia. And should you judge its actions\nto be wicked, you will strike it down.
As long its actions are just... Well, then it\ncan do whatever it pleases. I leave that\njudgment entirely to you.
Ha ha ha! Oh my, yes. That bit about\ncolonizing you was my little joke.\nBut you should have seen your faces!
There was no other retort to your speech.\nYou rendered a man of the sea speechless,\nand have the makings of a true hero.
Oh? I suspect it's your influence that\nturned my idiot of a son into the man who\nstands before me now.
Only a fool would separate him from you,\nand so I place him in the care of Saint\nLotier's newest allies.
Together with the mana of water,\nborn of mother sea.
Yesss! Now we can build a dracolith!
As the Waterwyrm's power grows,\nthe threat posed by the empire wanes.
Thank you, Zacharias. We are in your debt.
I give you my oath here and now that New\nAlberia will be an ally worthy of your trust!
Ya know, {player_name}?\nI think I was just runnin' away from\nwhat I didn't like this whole time.
Well, just...politics and all that. I probably\ncoulda hacked it if I'd actually tried.
I just never gave it a chance. Bein' with\nyou has made me see that.
You could do to learn from his example.
Anyway, does this mean you intend to\ninherit your father's post one day, Ranzal?\nWill you rule over Saint Lotier?
Pfft! Please. A city that size will run just\nfine on its own. I'm a...whatchacallit?\nAn integral asset of New Alberia!
And I'm ready to get back to whatever that\nis, so let's head home.
Rulin' stuff still ain't my thing, but buildin'\na kingdom with you don't sound half bad.
I have an update from the west,\nEmpress.
The Aquapolis, I take it? What is it?
They refuse to submit to imperial rule,\nand have instead chosen to make an\nalliance with the traitorous prince.
So my brother is now capturing the hearts\nof leaders as well as dragons? Impressive.
But the days of the Aquapolis are\nnumbered...and his along with them.
The great crimson flame that burns to the\nnorth can reduce even the heavens to ash,\nand soon it will devour them all...
